May 10, 2001


NTSB REVIEWS MOST WANTED SAFETY RECOMMENDATIONS, UPDATES FOR 2001

Washington, D.C. -- The National Transportation Safety Board holds a public
Board meeting Tuesday, May 15 at 9:30 a.m., at its Board Room and Conference
Center, 426 L'Enfant Plaza, S.W., Washington, D.C. The item on the agenda:
  The Board will review activity related to the 11 items on
last year's Most Wanted Safety Recommendations list and issue an updated
list for 2001.  The Safety Board established the Most Wanted Safety
Recommendations Program in 1990. The recommendations placed on this list are
selected by the Board as issues for intensified follow-up and to heighten
public awareness of these safety concerns.   Press Officer: Terry Williams
Directions to Board Room: Front door located on Lower 10th Street, directly
below L'Enfant Plaza. From Metro, exit L'Enfant Plaza station at 9th and D
Streets escalator, walk through shopping mall, at CVS store take escalator
down one level. Board room will be to your left.

Media Contact:  (202) 314-6100


